{'chapter_title': 'Bhagavad Gita: Chapter 7, Verse 12', 'sanskrit': ['ये चैव सात्त्विका भावा राजसास्तामसाश्च ये |', 'मत्त एवेति तान्विद्धि न त्वहं तेषु ते मयि || 12||'], 'latin': ['ye chaiva sāttvikā bhāvā rājasās tāmasāśh cha ye', 'matta eveti tān viddhi na tvahaṁ teṣhu te mayi'], 'translation': ['\r\n                            ', '\r\n                            The three states of material existence—goodness, passion, and ignorance—are manifested by my energy. They are in me, but I am beyond them.\r\n                        ']}